[
    {
        "content": "<p>I just realized record builders could be used to generate several random values at once, as long as each of them depend only on a seed and don't need each other:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Ruby\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"n\">generator</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"no\">Generator</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"no\">I32</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">b</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"no\">I32</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">c</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"no\">I32</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">}</span>\n<span class=\"n\">generator</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"no\">Random</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">map2</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">&lt;-</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"ss\">a</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"no\">Random</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">i32</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"ss\">b</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"no\">Random</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">i32</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"ss\">c</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"no\">Random</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">i32</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n<span class=\"p\">}</span>\n</code></pre></div>",
        "id": 492757294,
        "sender_full_name": "Richard Feldman",
        "timestamp": 1736438470
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>all we need to do is to introduce <code>Random.map2</code></p>",
        "id": 492757389,
        "sender_full_name": "Richard Feldman",
        "timestamp": 1736438494
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>no need to thread the seed through</p>",
        "id": 492757459,
        "sender_full_name": "Richard Feldman",
        "timestamp": 1736438514
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>this doesn't work if (for example) <code>b</code> needs to depend on <code>a</code>, but the common case we've been talking about is where we need to generate several values independently, which it turns out we can already do if we just add <code>Random.map2</code> <span aria-label=\"smiley\" class=\"emoji emoji-1f603\" role=\"img\" title=\"smiley\">:smiley:</span></p>",
        "id": 492757802,
        "sender_full_name": "Richard Feldman",
        "timestamp": 1736438597
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Yeah, I feel like this came up before. It maybe was an off hand suggested at one point. I remember seeing a record pattern match to access multiple generated values after a record builder.</p>",
        "id": 492759037,
        "sender_full_name": "Brendan Hansknecht",
        "timestamp": 1736438908
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Cause next line would be :</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Ruby\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">seed_</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span><span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">b</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">c</span><span class=\"p\">})</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"no\">Random</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">gen</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">seed_</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">generator</span>\n</code></pre></div>",
        "id": 492759390,
        "sender_full_name": "Brendan Hansknecht",
        "timestamp": 1736439003
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>yep!</p>",
        "id": 492759681,
        "sender_full_name": "Richard Feldman",
        "timestamp": 1736439081
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>although I do wonder how much seed threading we even need to do if we use record builders to batch stuff</p>",
        "id": 492759792,
        "sender_full_name": "Richard Feldman",
        "timestamp": 1736439114
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>might still be some, but probably significantly less</p>",
        "id": 492759819,
        "sender_full_name": "Richard Feldman",
        "timestamp": 1736439122
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Really depends how often rng is dependent.</p>",
        "id": 492760968,
        "sender_full_name": "Brendan Hansknecht",
        "timestamp": 1736439433
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Luke and I came to the same conclusion with roc-random: <a href=\"https://github.com/lukewilliamboswell/roc-random/blob/6260860c2e9c8cf52f6cd846583d4a005f4e6b9a/examples/color.roc#L12\">https://github.com/lukewilliamboswell/roc-random/blob/6260860c2e9c8cf52f6cd846583d4a005f4e6b9a/examples/color.roc#L12</a></p>",
        "id": 492783830,
        "sender_full_name": "Sam Mohr",
        "timestamp": 1736445548
    }
]